    "causal_summary": "The doc-accuracy iteration (iteration 9) was the largest confirmed-P1 spike in the review, landing in the second-to-last deep-dive iteration. It confirmed one shipped-code mislabel as P1 (the Memory rollup marks shipped phases as Planned) plus a 12-strong staleness cluster where the packet narrative docs disagree with committed code and with each other. A reader using these docs as the authoritative narrative would wrongly conclude the schema work and release-cleanup track made no progress. The mislabel misrepresents shipped scope at the canonical subsystem rollup; the cluster freezes the timeline and before-vs-after at commit 30 of 57 and understates the gated-but-shipped schema cluster.",
